section.p:
For instance, you can display the page counter at the bottom of each page, prefixed by the
        word 'Page' in the selected
          language:@page chapter {
  @bottom-center {
    content: oxy_xpath("if (@lang='es') then  'Página' \
                        else if (@lang='it') then 'Pagina' \
                        else 'Page'") " " counter(page);
  }
}Backslashes (\) are used to
          split the XPath into multiple lines to make it easier to read.

For example, you can display the language code in the top-right corner of each page,
        according to each topic
        language:*[class ~= "topic/topic"] {
  string-set: lang oxy_xpath("if (@lang) then upper-case(@lang) else 'EN'");
}

@page chapter {
  @top-right-corner {
    color: orange;
    content: string(lang);
  }
}
